<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--HeartTransplant     04-12 0095</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Heart Transplant,0098</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Jarvik-7 Recipient Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who was sustained six days by a Jarvik-7
artificial heart until undergoing a transplant has died.
   Ronald J. Gabriel, 38, of Arnold, died Sunday at
Presbyterian-University Hospital of Pittsburgh.
   Gabriel received the transplant April 7, six days after surgeons
implanted the mechanical heart. He had suffered a massive heart
attack March 30.
   Gabriel was the 18th person to receive an artificial heart at
the hospital, officials said Monday.
   Gabriel was a production underwriter for Pennsylvania National
Insurance Co. in Murrysville for 14 years.
</TEXT>
