<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Salvador-Recount,0199</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Arena Asks Vote Recount In Eastern El Salvador</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The rightist party that won
last month's legislative elections has filed a request for a vote
recount in La Union, the country's easternmost province.
   The Central Elections Council last week announced that the
rightist Nationalist Republican Alliance, or Arena, had won 30 of
60 seats in the unicameral legislature in nationwide elections held
March 20.
   All 60 seats in the Assembly were decided, as well as municipal
authorities in 262 towns and cities. The council said the incumbent
Christian Democratic Party won 23 Assembly seats and the National
Conciliation Party won seven.
   Arena, which won 178 of the municipalities, claimed it also
gained an outright majority in the Assembly. It charged the
Christian Democrats with trying to ``steal'' a deputy in La Union.
   Preliminary results from the province indicated Arena had taken
two of three deputy seats. But final results released by the
council gave only one to Arena and two to the Christian Democrats.
   Arena filed its request for a recount on Monday. The council has
until Wednesday to decided whether to grant or reject the request.
