<HEAD>Food Poisoning From Funeral Dinner Kills 14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Twenty-seven people who attended a dinner
following a funeral in northeastern China came down with food
poisoning and 14 of them died, the official China Daily reported
today.
   The 13 others became seriously ill after the dinner last week in
Yixian County, according to the report.
   The dinner was held by Yu Huqing, head of the gardening
department of Jinzhou City in Yixian County following the death of
his mother, the newspaper said. The report did not say if Yu was
among those who died.
