<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--RejectedSuitor     04-12 0136</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Rejected Suitor,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Jealous Suitor Blamed For Seven Deaths In Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire that killed seven members of a
family was blamed on a 49-year-old man whose proposal to marry the
family's 22-year-old daughter was turned down, police said today.
   The suspect, Muthaswamy Krishnan, was turned over to police by
neighbors who said he poured gasoline on the Sinathambi's home in
Kotagala village and set it ablaze, police Sgt. Nihal Muttabanda
said by telephone from the village.
   He said witnesses in the tea plantation village 55 miles east of
Colombo told him Krishnan was angry when he was rejected as a
suitor by the family's daughter, Padmini, and learned she was to
marry another man.
   Padmini, her father, mother and four brothers died in the blaze
on Monday, Muttabanda said.
</TEXT>
