<HEAD>Anita Page Taken To Hospital</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: CORRECTS spelling to Page, sted Paige throughout</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Anita Page, star of the 1929 film ``Broadway
Melody,'' was taken to a hospital by ambulance before the 60th
annual Academy Awards began Monday night, authorities said.
   ``We were near the door when she let out a moan and collapsed.
She was unconscious for about 10 minutes,'' said the actress'
husband, retired Rear Adm. Herschel House.
   ``She fainted,'' said a nursing coordinator at the Hospital of
the Good Samaritan who did not want her name used. ``She is here
and in stable condition. We ran some blood tests, but I can't give
you any more details.
   ``She will be discharged soon.''
   House said Miss Page might stay at the hospital overnight.
   ``We don't know what it was. Her vital signs are fine and she's
improving,'' her husband said.
   Miss Page, 77, made 33 films for Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer and was to
participate in a production number during Monday night's Oscar
broadcast that featured a representative from each of the 59 Best
Picture Academy Awards, said House.
   Miss Page and her husband live in Coronado, south of San Diego.
