<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Accident Arrest,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman in See-Through Clothes Arrested After Near-Wrecks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PEORIA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman in a see-through, fish-net body suit
disrupted traffic, caused several near-wrecks and ended up being
arrested, authorities said.
   Police said Dolly May Jane McCloud, 21, of East Peoria, was
arrested Saturday on charges of public indecency and disorderly
conduct, as well as obstructing police, authorities said.
   According to police, an unidentified driver reported several
motorists nearly collided when they suddenly slowed to look at Ms.
McCloud.
   Police Sgt. Phillip Benne said Ms. McCloud was wearing a
see-through, fish-net body suit that exposed her chest. She was
covered by other clothes from the waist down, Benne said.
   Benne said he saw three motorists slam on their brakes, honk
their horns and wave at Ms. McCloud, who was taken to the Peoria
County Jail and released after posting $100 cash bond. She is
scheduled to appear in court on May 2.
</TEXT>
