<HEAD>China Hires Firm As Billboard Consultant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SCRANTON, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   New billboards will soon be appearing along
China's road to a modern economy.
   Zhao Guihong, general manager for the China's National Outdoor
Advertising Agency, and Gerard P. Joyce, president of Patrick Media
Group, announced Monday that the firm would become a consultant to
China on billboards.
   China's consumers are very brand conscious, and companies that
want to sell in China must make their products visible, Joyce said.
Outdoor advertising represents about 25 percent of the advertising
dollar in China, compared to less than two percent in the United
States, he said.
   ``Our guests are seeking to learn more about marketing, advanced
creative and construction techniques, operations and current
research and development,'' Joyce said.
   Zhao, leading a five-member Chinese delegation on an eight-day,
six-city tour of Patrick Media's outdoor displays, plants and
facilities, said he looks forward to an informative and productive
long-term relationship with Patrick Media.
