<1ST_LINE>r a PM-ExecutiveFlees     04-12 0268</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Executive Flees,0277</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Executive and $1.3 Million Both Gone</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIVERIA BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A security company executive who left
a note behind saying he knew he was making a mistake is missing
along with $1.3 million.
   The money had been kept in a safe that could not be opened until
two days after John Anthony Quinn disappeared, Palm Beach County
sheriff's Lt. Gary Hill said Monday.
   Quinn disappeared Saturday after leaving the notefor his family.
   ``He said (in his note) he was making a mistake and he knew
it,'' Hill said. ``But he loved his family and hoped they would
forgive him and understand some day.''
   Quinn, 48, was vice president and general manager of Federal
Protection Services Inc., a security company with an armored car
division that transports money.
   Worried family members and co-workers called police Sunday after
spending more than 24 hours searching for Quinn.
   ``When the (security office) safe released, we discovered money
was missing and our theories about what happened to him were
confirmed. We have several leads to where he might have gone but
nothing positive,'' Hill said.
   Quinn's company car was found in the parking lot at Palm Beach
International Airport.
   Quinn was one of the few employees with access to the safe's
combination. Deputies said that worn cash scheduled to be destroyed
had been stored in the safe. They said the money _ in bills ranging
from fives to hundreds _ probably could not be traced.
   Quinn had been dogged by financial problems, and the Internal
Revenue Service had put liens on his wages and personal property,
deputies said.
</TEXT>
