<2ND_LINE>PM-Spain-Bomb,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bomb Explodes Outside Treasury Office in Barcelona</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BARCELONA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded early today outside a
Treasury Ministry office, slightly damaging a door and several
parked cars but causing no injuries, police said.
   Similar bombs placed outside doors of three other Treasury
Ministry offices in this northeastern city emitted smoke but failed
to go off, police said.
   No group immediately claimed responsibility for planting the
bombs, but police said they suspected Terra Lliure, a small
terrorist group that seeks independence for the four-province
northeastern region of Catalonia.
   Police said the bombing occurred just before 2 a.m. and
residents notified police of the other three bombs shortly
afterward.
   Barcelona is the largest city in the Catalonian region and
Spain's second-largest city.
   Terra Lliure, which stands for Free Land in the Catalan
language, has claimed numerous bombings in the region in the last
three years.
