<HEAD>Kuwait Airways Suspends Flights To Asia</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Hijack, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kuwait Airways today indefinitely
suspended all flights to and from Asia, the airline manager in
Thailand said.
   The manager, Elias H. Shiber, said he did not know whether the
decision was related to the hijacking of Kuwait Airways Flight 422.
No reason was given by the head office in Kuwait, he said.
   The plane was hijacked by armed men after it took off from
Bangkok for Kuwait on April 5.
   Shiber said that besides Thailand, the suspension affected
flights to and from Sri Lanka, Pakistan, India, Bangladesh, and the
Philippines.
   The last flight involving an Asian destination, he said, was
another Flight 422, which left Bangkok at 3 a.m. today for Kuwait.
</TEXT>
