<HEAD>Man Falls From Ambulance, Hitchhikes To Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AVELLINO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An injured man riding unattended in the
back of an ambulance fell out onto the road and had to hitchhike
the rest of the way to the hospital, Italian newspapers reported
today.
   The reports said Carmine Urciuolo, 23, a native of Avellino, 34
miles southeast of Naples, and the stretcher on which he lay fell
out of the ambulance because the driver had not correctly closed
the rear doors of the vehicle.
   Urciuolo had been injured in a traffic accident.
   Not until the ambulance reached the hospital emergency room did
the driver realize that the patient was no longer in the vehicle.
   Urciuolo hitchhiked to the hospital and was treated for minor
injuries.
