<HEAD>Eight Killed, 100 Left Homeless in Landslide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CUZCO, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tons of mud and rocks swept through a village
in the Andes, killing eight farmers and leaving more than 100
people homeless, civil defense officials said Tuesday.
   The landslide struck the tiny farming hamlet of Quellomayo,
about 350 miles southeast of Lima, Cuzco civil defense chief Col.
Victor Romero told The Associated Press.
   He said two people were injured and several homes and two
railroad bridges were destroyed in Monday's slide. Romero said the
disaster was caused by recent torrential rains.
