   Manufacturers Hanover Corp. plans to sell its
consumer finance unit for $685 million in cash to a unit of
American General Corp., a Texas-based financial service concern.
   The companies said Monday they reached an agreement in principle
on the sale of Manufacturers Hanover Consumer Services Inc. in a
deal that would nearly double the size of American General's
consumer credit operations.
