determined, Paretti said in the statement. He said, however, he was
considering diversifying Cannon through travel, real estate and
insurance operations in Europe.
   Cannon finances, produces and distributes films for theatrical
release and handles distribution for pay television and home video
markets. The company has been plagued by a lack of hit films in
recent years.
   The company has delayed reporting its fourth-quarter losses,
which company officials recently described as ``very substantial.''
Last year, the company said its losses for 1987 would surpass the
$60 million figure reported the previous year.
   Cannon also announced plans Monday to produce 20 feature films
next year.
   Among its recently completed works are ``Evil Angels'' with
Meryl Streep; ``Hanna's War'' with Ellen Burstyn, and ``Hero'' with
Chuck Norris.
