Hidegarde Zagorski, vice president of Prudential-Bache Securities
Inc.
   ``Once the selling is over, (stocks) will move into higher
ground,'' she said.
   Analysts noted that investors are awaiting the release of retail
sales figures on Wednesday and Thursday's report on merchandise
trade figures for February.
   ``A lot of people are going to play it close to the vest until
they see some direction from the numbers coming out,'' said Peter
Vandenberg, a vice president at Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc.
   Meanwhile, market participants were looking for ``cues from the
currency and bond markets,'' he said.
   Analysts also noted that investors are coming up against what
has become a psychological barrier at the 2,100-level on the Dow.
   ``The Dow has bumped its head against that level so many times,
so there is some hesitation'' when it approaches that level,
Zagorski said.
   Among the most actively traded issues, Stone Container was up 1\
to 33\; Digital Equipment was up ~ to 108}; Compaq Computer was up
| to 55], and Colt Industries was off 1 to 17\.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks fell
0.16 to 152.31. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up 1.03 at 304.72.
</TEXT>
